Why the examiner’s conclusion defeats §103

A §103 rejection requires an articulated reason why the claimed invention as a whole would have been obvious; the MPEP states that the key to a §103 rejection is a clear articulation of why the claimed invention would have been obvious.

Here, the examiner’s own statement confirms that the cited references lack the claimed core features. The cited arts may show additional information in an icon area, but they do not show or suggest the claimed technical architecture.

Therefore, the cited combination does not provide a prima facie basis for §103 unless the Office supplies a further teaching or reason to add those missing technical layers.


